# **Personal Portfolio Website (MERN Stack)**

## **Project Plan Report**

---

# 1. Project Overview

## Introduction

The **Personal Portfolio Website** is a full-stack web application developed using the **MERN Stack (MongoDB, Express.js, React.js, and Node.js)**. The project aims to create a modern, responsive, and professional platform for showcasing personal information, technical skills, projects, certifications, education, and contact details.

In addition to providing an engaging experience for visitors, the application includes a secure **Admin Dashboard** that allows the portfolio owner to manage website content without modifying the source code. The dashboard enables authenticated users to update portfolio information, manage projects, upload certificates, and review messages submitted through the contact form.

This project demonstrates practical knowledge of modern web development, RESTful APIs, database management, authentication, and deployment using cloud platforms.

---

# 2. Project Objectives

The primary objectives of this project are:

* Develop a responsive and user-friendly portfolio website.
* Showcase personal information, technical skills, and completed projects.
* Allow visitors to contact the portfolio owner through a contact form.
* Implement secure authentication for administrative access.
* Provide a dashboard for managing website content dynamically.
* Deploy the application using modern cloud hosting platforms.

---

# 3. Technology Stack

| Component       | Technology                                  |
| --------------- | ------------------------------------------- |
| Frontend        | React.js, React Router, Tailwind CSS, Axios |
| Backend         | Node.js, Express.js                         |
| Database        | MongoDB Atlas, Mongoose                     |
| Authentication  | JSON Web Token (JWT), bcrypt.js             |
| Deployment      | Vercel, Render, MongoDB Atlas               |
| Version Control | Git & GitHub                                |

